#: Game.Levels.FinsetInduction
msgid "# Finset Induction\n"
"\n"
"You now know how to manipulate sums and products algebraically â€”\n"
"splitting summands, factoring, swapping order, peeling terms off\n"
"ranges. But all of those tools work by applying *existing* identities.\n"
"\n"
"What if you need to prove a sum or product identity that isn't in\n"
"the library?\n"
"\n"
"**Finset induction** is the answer. Just as you prove statements\n"
"about natural numbers by induction on آ§0 (base case آ§1, step\n"
"آ§2), you can prove statements about finsets by induction\n"
"on آ§3:\n"
"\n"
"- **Base case**: prove the statement for آ§4\n"
"- **Inductive step**: given a finset آ§5 and a fresh element\n"
"  آ§6, assume the statement holds for آ§7 and prove it for\n"
"  آ§8\n"
"\n"
"The inductive step always follows the same **collect-and-close**\n"
"pattern:\n"
"1. **Collect** â€” peel with آ§9 (or آ§10),\n"
"   substitute the IH, peel cardinalities if needed\n"
"2. **Close** â€” finish the arithmetic with آ§11 or آ§12\n"
"\n"
"This world teaches the complete induction workflow for both sums\n"
"and products over arbitrary finsets.\n"
"\n"
"**Prerequisites**: آ§13, آ§14 from BigOpIntro,\n"
"آ§15 from BigOpAlgebra, and آ§16 from MeetFin."
msgstr ""

