#: Game.Levels.FinNavigation
msgid "# Navigating Fin\n"
"\n"
"You've learned to construct and compare elements of آ§0. Now\n"
"you'll learn to *navigate* within آ§1 â€” accessing specific\n"
"landmark elements and moving between آ§2 and آ§3.\n"
"\n"
"Three functions form the navigation toolkit:\n"
"\n"
"**آ§4** â€” the maximum element of آ§5, with\n"
"value آ§6. It's the boundary element, sitting at the top.\n"
"\n"
"**آ§7** â€” embeds آ§8 into آ§9 by keeping\n"
"the same value but relaxing the bound. If آ§10 has value\n"
"آ§11, then آ§12 also has value آ§13.\n"
"\n"
"**آ§14** â€” moves forward: if آ§15 has value آ§16,\n"
"then آ§17 has value آ§18.\n"
"\n"
"Both آ§19 and آ§20 send آ§21 â€” they\n"
"increase the type's size by 1 â€” but they do different things to\n"
"the value: آ§22 preserves it, آ§23 increments it.\n"
"\n"
"(This is why آ§24 starts at 0: the embedding آ§25\n"
"preserves values exactly, and آ§26 increments by exactly 1. With\n"
"1-indexing, these clean relationships would need offsets.)\n"
"\n"
"The central insight of this world: آ§27 has **two**\n"
"decompositions:\n"
"- Every element is either آ§28 or آ§29\n"
"  for some آ§30 (**castSucc/last**)\n"
"- Every element is either آ§31 or آ§32\n"
"  for some آ§33 (**0/succ**)\n"
"\n"
"These dual decompositions will power the two ways to build\n"
"tuples in the next world.\n"
"\n"
"In this world, you'll learn to:\n"
"- Compute the value of آ§34, آ§35, and آ§36 using their\n"
"  val lemmas\n"
"- Prove that آ§37 never reaches آ§38 (and آ§39 never\n"
"  reaches آ§40)\n"
"- Prove that both آ§41 and آ§42 are injective\n"
"- Prove both the castSucc/last and 0/succ decompositions\n"
"- Prove that آ§43 hits every non-last element (surjectivity)\n"
"- Combine all of this in the boss"
msgstr ""

