#: Game.Levels.FinsetOperations.L08_Extensionality
msgid "The آ§0 tactic is the standard way to prove finset equality in Lean.\n"
"The pattern:\n"
"\n"
"1. آ§1 â€” introduces a variable آ§2 and converts آ§3 to آ§4\n"
"2. آ§5 â€” splits the biconditional into two implications\n"
"3. Prove each direction\n"
"\n"
"In this level, the hypotheses آ§6 and آ§7 handed you the\n"
"implications directly. In the next level, you'll prove an abstract\n"
"set identity where you need to do the element-chasing yourself.\n"
"\n"
"The key insight: *finsets are determined by their elements*. This is\n"
"the **extensionality principle** â€” two collections are equal when they\n"
"have the same members.\n"
"\n"
"**آ§8 as a transferable strategy**: This is the third time you've\n"
"used آ§9, and each time it does the same thing in a different context:\n"
"- **Fin elements** (MeetFin L15): آ§10 reduces آ§11 to آ§12\n"
"  â€” two indices are equal when their values are equal\n"
"- **Functions** (FinTuples L12): آ§13 reduces آ§14 to آ§15\n"
"  â€” two functions are equal when they agree at every input\n"
"- **Finsets** (this level): آ§16 reduces آ§17 to آ§18\n"
"  â€” two sets are equal when they have the same elements\n"
"\n"
"The unifying principle: **ext reduces equality of structured types to\n"
"equality of components**. Whenever you see آ§19 for a structured\n"
"type, try آ§20 â€” it will find the right decomposition automatically.\n"
"\n"
"**Why extensionality?** This is a design choice, not an inevitability.\n"
"A list like آ§21 is different from آ§22 â€” lists track\n"
"multiplicity and order. A *multiset* like آ§23 differs from\n"
"آ§24 â€” multisets track multiplicity but not order. A finset\n"
"like آ§25 equals آ§26 â€” finsets track neither multiplicity\n"
"nor order, only *which elements are present*. Extensionality is what\n"
"makes a finset a finset rather than a list or multiset.\n"
"\n"
"**The ext-unfold-logic recipe**: From now on, most set identity proofs\n"
"will follow the same three-phase pattern:\n"
"1. **ext** â€” آ§27 reduces set equality to element-wise logic\n"
"2. **unfold** â€” آ§28, آ§29, etc.\n"
"   (or آ§30) to convert membership into pure logic\n"
"3. **logic** â€” آ§31, آ§32, آ§33/آ§34,\n"
"   آ§35/آ§36 to prove the resulting propositional equivalence\n"
"\n"
"We'll call this the **ext-unfold-logic** recipe. Every set identity in\n"
"the remaining levels follows this recipe. When you see a finset equality\n"
"to prove, think 'ext-unfold-logic' and the three steps will guide you."
msgstr ""

