#: Game.Levels.BinomialTheorem
msgid "# The Binomial Theorem\n"
"\n"
"Why are آ§0 called **binomial** coefficients? Because they\n"
"are the coefficients when you expand a **binomial** (two-term sum)\n"
"raised to a power:\n"
"\n"
"آ§1\n"
"\n"
"This identity is the **binomial theorem**. It connects the algebraic\n"
"operation of raising a sum to a power with the combinatorial operation\n"
"of choosing subsets.\n"
"\n"
"In the BinomialCoefficients world, you proved identities about\n"
"آ§2 using its recursive definition (Pascal's identity).\n"
"In the Powerset world, you saw that آ§3 counts the\n"
"آ§4-element subsets of an آ§5-element set.\n"
"\n"
"Now you will see the **third face** of binomial coefficients: their\n"
"role as coefficients in polynomial expansion. By plugging in specific\n"
"values of آ§6 and آ§7, the binomial theorem generates counting\n"
"identities for free:\n"
"\n"
"- آ§8: the **row sum** آ§9\n"
"- آ§10: the **weighted sum** آ§11\n"
"- آ§12 (over آ§13): the **alternating sum** آ§14\n"
"\n"
"The key new proof pattern is **specialization**: start with the\n"
"general آ§15, plug in specific values, simplify the summand\n"
"using آ§16 and آ§17, and read off the identity.\n"
"\n"
"**Prerequisites**: آ§18 from BigOpAlgebra,\n"
"آ§19 identities from BinomialCoefficients,\n"
"آ§20 and آ§21 from Powerset."
msgstr ""

