"\n"
"The **pigeonhole principle** says: if you have آ§0 pigeons\n"
"and only آ§1 pigeonholes, at least two pigeons must share a hole.\n"
"The name comes from the image of pigeons roosting: with more\n"
"birds than holes, some hole gets crowded.\n"
"\n"
"More precisely: any function آ§2 with آ§3\n"
"fails to be injective â€” there exist distinct آ§4 with\n"
"آ§5.\n"
"\n"
"Before tackling the full 3-pigeons-2-holes version, let's practice\n"
"the pattern on the simplest case: **2 pigeons, 1 hole**.\n"
"\n"
"Any function آ§6 must send two different inputs\n"
"to the same output. Why? Because آ§7 has only ONE element\n"
"(the value آ§8), so both آ§9 and آ§10 must equal آ§11.\n"
"\n"
"**Strategy**:\n"
"1. The witnesses are آ§12 and آ§13 (the two inputs)\n"
"2. They're different (the inequality آ§14)\n"
"3. Both map to the unique output\n"
"\n"
"The 'classify + compare' pattern:\n"
"- Every آ§15 element is آ§16 (classify)\n"
"- So آ§17 and آ§18 (compare)\n"
"- Therefore آ§19 (collision found)"
