#: Game.Levels.FinsetImage.L10_ImageIntersectionCounterexample
msgid "You've proved that the containment آ§0\n"
"can be **strict** when آ§1 is not injective.\n"
"\n"
"**The phantom witness phenomenon**: The element آ§2 in\n"
"آ§3 is a **phantom** â€” it looks like it belongs to\n"
"the image of the intersection, but it doesn't. Why? Because the\n"
"witnesses that produce it are *different*: آ§4 maps to آ§5,\n"
"and آ§6 maps to آ§7, but آ§8, so there's no single\n"
"element in آ§9 that maps to آ§10.\n"
"\n"
"**Why union works but intersection doesn't**: Compare the two results:\n"
"\n"
"- آ§11 â€” **exact equality**, always.\n"
"- آ§12 â€” **only containment** in general.\n"
"\n"
"For union, if آ§13, the witness آ§14 that maps to آ§15\n"
"is in آ§16 or آ§17, so it's in آ§18. No phantom is possible â€” the\n"
"single witness suffices.\n"
"\n"
"For intersection, آ§19 gives you **two** witnesses:\n"
"آ§20 and آ§21 with آ§22. Unless آ§23 (which\n"
"injectivity guarantees), these witnesses are useless for proving\n"
"آ§24.\n"
"\n"
"The structural reason: image is 'surjective onto its own elements' â€”\n"
"every element of آ§25 has a preimage by definition. Union only needs\n"
"*existence* of a preimage (one witness anywhere), which image always\n"
"provides. Intersection needs a *shared* preimage (one witness in both\n"
"sets), which image can't guarantee without injectivity."
msgstr ""

