#: Game.Levels.FinsetOperations.L24_DualDistributivity
msgid "You've proved the **dual distributivity** law:\n"
"آ§0.\n"
"\n"
"Was it really 'the same proof pattern, swapping آ§1 and آ§2'?\n"
"Almost â€” the forward direction was parallel (case-split, rebuild\n"
"with آ§3), but the backward direction required a\n"
"**nested case-split**: splitting on آ§4, then conditionally\n"
"splitting on آ§5. This asymmetry is the difference between\n"
"distributing آ§6 over آ§7 (needs one case-split) and\n"
"آ§8 over آ§9 (needs nested case-splits).\n"
"\n"
"Together, Levels 23 and 24 show that union and intersection distribute\n"
"over each other in both directions â€” this is the defining property\n"
"of a **distributive lattice**, a structure you'll revisit in the\n"
"orders and lattices course.\n"
"\n"
"**A deeper connection**: You proved both distributivity laws from\n"
"scratch using آ§10 + logic. In fact, either one follows from the\n"
"other via De Morgan's law. De Morgan *dualizes* آ§11 and آ§12,\n"
"converting one distributivity law into the other. This means the\n"
"two laws are not independent â€” they're two faces of the same coin.\n"
"The proof-from-scratch approach is more instructive (it exercises\n"
"the logic directly), but the derivation via De Morgan shows the\n"
"structural economy underneath.\n"
"\n"
"**The duality principle**: Look back at the identities you've proved\n"
"in this world. They come in pairs:\n"
"\n"
"| Identity | Dual |\n"
"|---|---|\n"
"| آ§13 | آ§14 |\n"
"| آ§15 | آ§16 |\n"
"| آ§17 | آ§18 |\n"
"| آ§19 | آ§20 |\n"
"| آ§21 | آ§22 |\n"
"\n"
"The pattern: swap آ§23 (equivalently,\n"
"آ§24, or آ§25),\n"
"and you get the dual identity. This is not a coincidence â€” it's a\n"
"theorem. In any **Boolean algebra** (and finsets form one), every\n"
"identity has a valid dual obtained by this swap. Once you prove\n"
"commutativity of آ§26, you *know* commutativity of آ§27 holds\n"
"by the same argument with the roles swapped.\n"
"\n"
"This duality is exactly what the lattice notation آ§28/آ§29\n"
"(Level 16) captures: the abstract lattice axioms are self-dual, so\n"
"every theorem about آ§30 has a mirror theorem about آ§31.\n"
"\n"
"Next: the boss, which integrates set difference with the\n"
"unfold-to-logic recipe."
msgstr ""

