msgid "# The Capstone Theorem\n"
"\n"
"You've assembled all the pieces. Now for the punchline.\n"
"\n"
"For finite types, **injectivity implies surjectivity**. If\n"
"آ§0 is injective (different inputs give different\n"
"outputs), then آ§1 is also surjective (every output is hit).\n"
"\n"
"Why? The image آ§2 satisfies:\n"
"- It has آ§3 elements (by آ§4, since آ§5 is injective)\n"
"- It is a subset of آ§6 (by آ§7, since everything\n"
"  lives in the universe)\n"
"\n"
