#: Game.Levels.PsetFin.L17_Pigeonhole
msgid "# Three Pigeons, Two Holes\n"
"\n"
"The **pigeonhole principle** says: if you put more objects into\n"
"fewer boxes, at least two objects share a box.\n"
"\n"
"Formally: any function آ§0 must send two\n"
"different inputs to the same output. There are 3 inputs but\n"
"only 2 possible outputs, so a collision is inevitable.\n"
"\n"
"This is your first real **theorem from combinatorics** â€” and\n"
"you can prove it using only the tools from Phase 1.\n"
"\n"
"**Strategy**:\n"
"1. Classify each آ§1 value: every آ§2 is either آ§3 or آ§4\n"
"2. Apply the classification to آ§5 and آ§6\n"
"3. If they're equal: witnesses are آ§7 and آ§8\n"
"4. If they differ: check آ§9 â€” it must match one of them"
msgstr ""

