#: Game.Levels.BigOpAlgebra.L15_RingTactic
msgid "# ring: Closing Algebraic Goals\n"
"\n"
"After transforming sums with big-operator lemmas, you often end up\n"
"with a goal that is pure algebra â€” rearranging additions and\n"
"multiplications. The آ§0 tactic closes such goals automatically.\n"
"\n"
"**What آ§1 can do**:\n"
"- آ§2 âœ“\n"
"- آ§3 âœ“\n"
"- Commutativity, associativity, distributivity âœ“\n"
"\n"
"**What آ§4 cannot do**:\n"
"- Anything involving hypotheses (it only looks at the goal)\n"
"- Anything involving آ§5, آ§6, membership, or non-ring operations\n"
"\n"
"So آ§7 complements the big-operator lemmas: the lemmas reduce\n"
"sum expressions to algebraic form, and آ§8 closes the algebra.\n"
"\n"
"There is also آ§9, which normalizes ring expressions without\n"
"necessarily closing the goal. Use آ§10 when آ§11 alone\n"
"doesn't close the goal but you want to simplify the algebra.\n"
"\n"
"**آ§12 vs آ§13**: You already know آ§14 from earlier worlds.\n"
"The distinction: آ§15 handles **linear** arithmetic over آ§16\n"
"and آ§17 â€” it can use hypotheses and solve آ§18 or\n"
"آ§19, but it cannot handle multiplication of variables\n"
"or exponents. آ§20 handles **polynomial** identities over any\n"
"commutative (semi)ring â€” it can expand آ§21 and collect\n"
"like terms, but it ignores all hypotheses. Use آ§22 for linear\n"
"goals with hypotheses; use آ§23 for algebraic identities.\n"
"\n"
"**The two-phase pattern**:\n"
"1. Use big-operator lemmas to transform sums\n"
"2. Use آ§24 to close the resulting algebra\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove the square-of-sum identity for big operators.\n"
"First use آ§25 to eliminate the آ§26 expression,\n"
"then close with آ§27. The resulting identity â€”\n"
"آ§28 â€” is the kind of algebraic\n"
"rearrangement آ§29 excels at."
msgstr ""

