"- **آ§11**: a set with آ§12 elements has آ§13 subsets\n"
"- **آ§14**: the subsets of آ§15 with exactly آ§16 elements\n"
"- **آ§17**: the count of آ§18-element subsets is آ§19\n"
"\n"
"This connects the *set-theoretic* operation (listing subsets) to the\n"
"*combinatorial* numbers (binomial coefficients) that you studied in the\n"
"BinomialCoefficients world. There, آ§20 was defined recursively\n"
"via Pascal's identity. Here, you'll see its **counting meaning**: it counts\n"
"the آ§21-element subsets.\n"
"\n"
"**Prerequisites**: آ§22 for subset reasoning, آ§23 from\n"
"Cardinality, and آ§24 identities from BinomialCoefficients."
msgstr ""

